  "CEILING": "Synthesis of OUR surface gap (scRNA atlas) + FIELD's published HLA-LOH calls (WGS) \u2014 different modalities, different patients, same cancer types. Patient-level not clonal (subclonal LOH => true addressable is LOWER; TRACERx ~76% of LUAD LOH subclonal). Lung is NSCLC-pooled, not LUAD. A*02 group match (A2 Bio is A*02:01). NOT a wet result.",
  "INTERPRETATION": "any-HLA-LOH (some allele-specific gate in principle) gives a generous ceiling; the ACTUAL single-allele A*02 Tmod gate addresses ~3-6% of patients (5-9x smaller) because it needs loss of the SPECIFIC sensed allele. The 100% gap barely moves for a single-allele gate. Implication: a PANEL of allele-specific blockers (A*02 + B*07 + ...) is needed to recover the any-HLA-LOH ceiling. This is the next design step."
